@10001 = ~Lord Leoncourt's treasure chest.

Today I met Durnkrag, a dwarven paladin, and his band of fellow adventurers in the Copper Coronet. They are looking for a treasure chest that was stolen from Lord Thaddeus Leoncourt of Baldur's Gate. A fence named Grudin may know something, but they are having difficulties locating him. Perhaps other fences will know where to find him. Once I locate him, I should return to Durnkrag.~
@10002 = ~Lord Leoncourt's treasure chest.

This night I have finally encountered Grudin. Unfortunately, so did another band, who calls themselves the Shadow Pack. They killed Grudin as I approached, but the fellow mentioned someone named Captain Randall, before he died. Now I should return to the Copper Coronet. Hopefully, this will be enough for Durnkrag.~
@10003 = ~Lord Leoncourt's treasure chest.

Upon hearing the news, Durnkrag and his friends, who call themselves the Dungeon Crawlers, headed for the docks immediately, and bade me to follow.~
@10004 = ~Lord Leoncourt's treasure chest.

Upon arriving to the docks, I found the Shadow Pack and the Dungeon Crawlers locked in mortal combat. I chose to assist Durnkrag, and the Shadow Pack decided to flee. Now to speak with Captain Randall...~
@10005 = ~Lord Leoncourt's treasure chest.

Upon arriving to the docks, I found the Shadow Pack and the Dungeon Crawlers locked in mortal combat. I chose to assist Ganelon, the leader of the Shadow Pack, and the Dungeon Crawlers decided to flee. Now to speak with Captain Randall...~
@10006 =  ~Lord Leoncourt's treasure chest.

Captain Randall asked for a fee of two thousand gold for the passage. Should I be willing to go, I must pay my half: one thousand gold.~
@10007 =  ~Lord Leoncourt's treasure chest.

We woke up on the cold dungeon floor. Apparently, Randall drugged us, with the intent to deliver us as slaves for the local smugglers. We decided to split up, to find Lord Leoncourt's chest and the exit as soon as possible.~
@10008 =  ~Lord Leoncourt's treasure chest.

A strange creature, half-rabbit, half-demon by the name of Lepus, with an uncanny liking for pants, was lurking with the chest in the ritual chamber. We defeated it, and Ganelon teleported us back to Athkatla. However, instead of treasure, we discovered a pair of Golden Pantaloons, and Ganelon fled in disgust.~
@10009 =  ~Lord Leoncourt's treasure chest.

